parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty starter relay can cause intermittent starting issues, leading to safety hazards, especially when the auto start/stop feature shuts down the engine at a stop light and the car fails to restart.
symptoms: but the starter does not engage
and the engine does not attempt to crank; a warning lamp may appear saying "auto start/stop unavailable".

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Seatbelts and Airbags to Deploy
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of seatbelts to lock and airbags to deploy in the event of an accident can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: as the issue is related to the failure of safety features during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system failure can cause the vehicle to stall or become stuck, leaving the driver stranded and potentially in danger.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or stops running while in motion
and the driver is unable to put the car in neutral to push it out of the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system issues can cause various problems, including starting issues, fuel system failures, and other safety hazards.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience intermittent starting issues

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel line can cause a significant amount of gasoline to leak onto the engine and surrounding areas, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to an engine compartment fire.
symptoms: Strong odor of gasoline in the cockpit
visible trail of fluid on the driveway
gasoline pooling on the engine and surrounding areas

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Oil Pump Failure Leading to Sudden Engine Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pump can cause the engine to suddenly die, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The "Service Electronic Throttle Control" light comes on
the vehicle goes into limp mode
the engine dies or loses power
the vehicle slows down or stalls
the engine fails to recover after stalling.
